OL,3,CMilitary families to be compensated
OL,4,Cfor serious water outage after MoD
OL,5,Cdispute
OL,7,FSouth West Water agreed to pay #250
OL,8,Fcompensation per household but as the
OL,9,FMoD is the billpayer for service
OL,10,Fhouseholds, no compensation could be
OL,11,Fpaid directly to those residents.
OL,13,FFred Thomas, MP for Plymouth Moor
OL,14,FView, says the MoD then stated that it
OL,15,Fwas not its policy to provide
OL,16,Fcompensation if the outage was for
OL,17,Fless than seven days.
